\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 214. C. baldaccii} Degen ex Bald.,{\i  Malpighia}{\b  9}: 277 (1895). Perennial, with short rhizome. Stems very stout. Leaves linear lanceolate in outline, entire or lyrate, with undulate margin, arachnoid-tomentose, shortly petiolate. Involucre 6-8 mm in diameter, ovoid; appendages long-decurrent, dark brown; fimbriae shorter than the width of the margin, silvery. Florets cream. Achenes c. 3 mm; pappus C. 1 mm.{\i  Alpine pastures. • W. Kriti.} Cr.
