\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 215. C. pindicola} Griseb., {\i Reise Rumel.}{\b  2}: 164 (1841). Perennial with short rhizome. Stems up to 15 cm. Lower leaves lyrate-pinnatisect with 2-3(-4) lobes on each side, petiolate; cauline entire or weakly dentate, decurrent. Involucre 16-18 mm in diameter, ovoid; appendages broadly decurrent, black; fimbriae silvery-white at apex. Florets cream. Pappus 1-1·5 mm. •{\i  Mountains of S.W. part of Balkan peninsula.} Al Gr Ju.
